Class TexturedMesh

  • java.lang.Object
    • javafx.scene.Node
      • javafx.scene.shape.Shape3D
        • javafx.scene.shape.MeshView
          • org.fxyz3d.shapes.primitives.TexturedMesh
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    javafx.css.Styleable, javafx.event.EventTarget, TextureMode
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    BezierMesh, ConeMesh, CSGMesh, CuboidMesh, CurvedSpringMesh, FrustumMesh, IcosahedronMesh, KnotMesh, PrismMesh, SegmentedSphereMesh, SegmentedTorusMesh, SpringMesh, SurfacePlotMesh, TetrahedraMesh, TriangulatedMesh

    public abstract class TexturedMesh
extends javafx.scene.shape.MeshView
implements TextureMode
    TexturedMesh is a base class that provides support for different mesh implementations taking into account four different kind of textures - None - Image - Colored vertices - Colored faces For the last two ones, number of colors and density map have to be provided Any subclass must use mesh, listVertices and listFaces
